ses, and containing ample discussions of conjectures and interpretations of earlier scholars. This book is an indispensable working tool for scholars using the new Teubner edition of the Life of Apollonius. It also caters for the needs of students of Greek language and literature in general, and especially of those interested in the Second Sophistic and the works of Flavius Philostratus.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aTextkritik. 4aZweite Sophistik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aSecond Sophistic.  atextual criticism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishz978311131908708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023z9783111318110oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311124365840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311124466240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111244662423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111244662/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-131908-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023